## Phase Rules

### One Phase at a Time

- Reduce work to **one implementation phase** with 2-4 related tasks, clear file set, reviewer checklist, and integration checks
- Route to **exactly one primary executor** unless genuine architectural uncertainty exists
- Reuse same worker `SESSION_ID` for follow-up fixes on the same phase, send **deltas only**

### Phase Shape

Every phase must have:
- Clear goal (one sentence)
- Explicit file set (modify/create)
- 2-4 related tasks
- Acceptance criteria (testable)
- Reviewer checklist
- Integration checks

### Avoid Anti-Patterns

- No two-pass tasks where one worker drafts and Claude rewrites
- No full CP0 discovery blobs when phase-scoped bundles suffice
- No `CROSS_VALIDATION` as default - use only when narrowing fails
- No re-explaining the whole plan to workers

### Context Sharing

- Turn CP0 findings into reusable context artifacts
- Build one phase-scoped context bundle per phase
- Same-phase follow-ups send deltas only
